      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why A-Ending Words Matter in Scrabble</h2>
      <p>Words ending in A serve a dual purpose on the Scrabble board. First, they're excellent vowel dumps — when your rack is clogged with vowels, A-ending words like TIARA, AQUA, and OKRA help you shed excess letters while still scoring. Second, A is one of the most hookable endings in the game. Many words can have an S added after the final A (PIZZA → PIZZAS), extending your scoring options on subsequent turns.</p>
      <p>The real power comes from pairing the A ending with high-value consonants earlier in the word. PIZZA (25 points), PIAZZA (26 points), and YAKUZA (22 points) all exploit this pattern — the Z tiles do the heavy scoring while the A provides a natural ending. Similarly, words like VODKA and QUOTA combine the soft A landing with K (5 pts) and Q (10 pts) for efficient scoring from common rack combinations.</p>

